            <p>Sitting at the crossroads of two ancient highways — the Great North Road and the Fosse Way — Newark-on-Trent has been a place of importance for nearly a thousand years. Its magnificent castle, granted a charter in the 12th century, witnessed the death of King John in 1216 and withstood three sieges during the English Civil War.</p>
            <p>Today, Newark is a thriving market town of around 42,000 people, proud of its heritage and buzzing with independent shops, excellent food and drink, and a calendar packed with events. The cobbled Market Square remains the heart of the town, as it has been for centuries.</p>
